good guide for dealing with common problem behaviors this is a clear , well written guide to dealing with behaviors every parent faces . it offers sound advice on how to deal with behaviors from whining to bullying and when to seek professional help . advice is presented well with main points highlighted and clear examples of how to apply the advice . it was extremely well laid out and easy to read . i particularly enjoyed the information on causes of behaviors as well as dealing with them . by the end of the book , parents have a clear idea of how to figure out what is causing a behavior and have some suggestions on how to change or eliminate the behavior